main event: Two observations of black smoke-like objects were observed on successive evenings over an international airport in Washington, D.C. in 1963.
interesting points: The objects were observed moving and changing direction.
The objects may have been aircraft or balloons, but there was insufficient data to evaluate.
The objects disappeared behind clouds and then reappeared, moving at a fast speed.
The objects made no sound and were described as bright white in color.
The observer estimated the objects were 1-2 miles away and moving rapidly.
